          "TITLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                " Fast neutron induced ((n,t) + (n,n't)) reaction cross",
                " sections in the medium and heavy mass regions"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "FACILITY": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "facility": [
                  "CYCLO"
                ],
                "institute": "2GERJUL"
              },
              "free_text": [
                "    Cyclotron."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "incident_source": [
                  "D-BE"
                ],
                "reaction": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                "     Deuteron-beryllium. 53 MeV deuteron."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SPECT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                " Identical nature of the neutron spectrum with the one",
                " at KFK cyclotron was confirmed.  Maximum intensity was",
                " at E(n) = 22.5 MeV, and 80% of the neutrons",
                " lie within the energy range of 14 to 30 MeV, giving",
                " thereby E(n) = 22 +- 8 MeV.",
                ".Irradiations were carried out for 6 to 10 hr at",
                " neutron flux densities of (2 to 5) x 10**10/cm2/sec.",
                "  Neutron spectrum provided by S.M.Qaim ( 29-12-2016):",
                "  units: energy - MeV, yield - 10**8n/(muC*MeV*sr)",
                " Energy   Neutron yield       Energy   Neutron yield",
                "  12.5     124.                 29.5      140.",
                "  13.5     158.                 30.5      115.",
                "  14.5     175.                 31.5      102.",
                "  15.5     199.                 32.5       85.",
                "  16.5     196.                 33.5       76.",
                "  17.5     208.                 34.5       58.",
                "  18.5     232.                 35.5       56.",
                "  19.5     251.                 36.5       47.",
                "  20.5     260.                 37.5       46.",
                "  22.5     259.                 38.5       40.",
                "  23.5     246.                 39.5       34.",
                "  24.5     238.                 40.5       31.",
                "  25.5     219.                 41.5       27.",
                "  26.5     192.                 42.5       24.",
                "  27.5     172.                 43.5       21.",
                "  28.5     152."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "REL-REF": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "code": "R",
                "subentry_number": "O1924002",
                "author": "G.W.Schweimer",
                "reference": {
                  "code": "J,NP/A,100,537,1967",
                  "field": {
                    "reference_type": "J",
                    "reference": {
                      "code": "NP/A",
                      "number": null,
                      "volume": "100",
                      "part": null,
                      "issue": null,
                      "page": "537"
                    },
                    "date": 1967
                  }
                }
              },
              "free_text": [
                "",
                "    Ref. for neutron spectrum"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                " High purity target material sealed under vacuum in a",
                " quartz ampoule. Au monitor foil was wrapped around."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "ACTIV"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                "    Activation.  Because (n,n pn), (n,p2n),",
                " (n,n d) and (n,dn) processes, which lead to the same",
                " product nucleus as the (n,t) reaction, are also",
                " energetically possible, radiochemical determination of",
                " the produced tritium was therefore necessary."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SCIN"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                "    Tri-Carb scintillation spectrometer.",
                " Typical liquid mixtures were,  H2O(+HTO)=10%,",
                " Scintillator solution =90%.",
                " The scintillator solution was made by dissolving 100 g",
                " naphthalene, 7 g 2,5-diphenyloxazol(ppo) and 0.3 g",
                " 2,2-p-phenylen-bis(5-phenyloxazol)(popop) in 1 litre",
                " p-dioxane."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "MONITOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": null,
                "reaction": {
                  "code": "79-AU-197(N,2N)79-AU-196,,SIG",
                  "code_unit": [
                    {
                      "unit": "79-AU-197(N,2N)79-AU-196,,SIG",
                      "field": {
